; basic_transactions.journal
; Covers the most common everyday transaction patterns:
;   - Opening balances (auto-balancing equity posting)
;   - Cleared (*) and pending (!) status flags
;   - Transaction codes in parentheses
;   - Simple expense & income entries
;   - Internal transfers
;   - Credit card usage and repayment
;   - Loan drawdown and repayment
;   - Cash withdrawal

; ── Opening balances ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; Auto-balancing equity posting: no amount on the last line.
; The parser must infer it as the negated sum of all other postings.
2026-01-01 Opening balance
    assets:bank:checking      50000.00 SEK
    assets:bank:savings       20000.00 SEK
    assets:cash                2000.00 SEK
    liabilities:credit-card   -5000.00 SEK
    equity:opening-balance

; ── Income ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; Cleared transaction: all postings explicitly balanced.
2026-01-25 * Salary January
    assets:bank:checking      35000.00 SEK
    income:salary            -35000.00 SEK

2026-02-25 * Salary February
    assets:bank:checking      35000.00 SEK
    income:salary            -35000.00 SEK

; Interest on savings account.
2026-02-28 * SEB Bank | Savings interest
    assets:bank:savings          85.50 SEK
    income:interest             -85.50 SEK

; ── Expenses ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; Pending transaction: awaiting settlement.
2026-01-28 ! Rent February
    expenses:housing:rent     12000.00 SEK
    assets:bank:checking     -12000.00 SEK

; Transaction with a reference code.
2026-01-30 * (POS-20260130-001) Hemköp | Groceries
    expenses:food:groceries     850.50 SEK
    liabilities:credit-card    -850.50 SEK

; Auto-balancing posting: parser infers assets:bank:checking amount.
2026-02-01 Spotify AB | Monthly subscription
    expenses:entertainment      119.00 SEK
    assets:bank:checking

; Split expense across two categories in one transaction.
2026-02-05 Restaurant dinner — split bill
    expenses:food:restaurants   400.00 SEK
    expenses:entertainment      200.00 SEK
    liabilities:credit-card    -600.00 SEK

; Four-posting transaction split over multiple expense accounts.
2026-02-14 Supermarket — weekly shop
    expenses:food:groceries    1200.00 SEK
    expenses:health              95.00 SEK
    expenses:entertainment       55.00 SEK
    liabilities:credit-card   -1350.00 SEK

; ── Transfers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; Internal transfer between asset accounts.
2026-02-10 Transfer checking → savings
    assets:bank:savings       10000.00 SEK
    assets:bank:checking     -10000.00 SEK

; Cash withdrawal from ATM.
2026-03-25 ATM withdrawal
    assets:cash                1000.00 SEK
    assets:bank:checking      -1000.00 SEK

; ── Credit card ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; Credit card repayment reduces the liability to zero.
2026-03-10 * Credit card bill payment March
    liabilities:credit-card    6950.50 SEK
    assets:bank:checking      -6950.50 SEK

; ── Loan ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; Loan drawdown creates a new liability and credits the bank account.
2026-03-15 Personal loan disbursement
    assets:bank:checking      50000.00 SEK
    liabilities:loan         -50000.00 SEK

; Loan repayment: principal, interest, and bank charge split across postings.
2026-03-20 Loan repayment March
    liabilities:loan           1500.00 SEK
    expenses:utilities          350.00 SEK
    expenses:bank-charges        25.00 SEK
    assets:bank:checking      -1875.00 SEK

; ── Rent (now cleared) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; The January pending rent clears in March.
2026-03-01 * Rent February — cleared
    liabilities:credit-card       0.00 SEK
    expenses:housing:rent         0.00 SEK
